{
  "texts": [
    "Contrary to what would seem logical, 1 × 1 convolutions are significantly more affordable than 5 × 5 convolution layers, and the fewer input streams also aid.",
    "But keep in mind that the 1 × 1 convolution is added after the max pooling layer, not before [99].• Inception V1 It performs convolution on the input with 3 different size i.e.",
    "(1 × 1, 3 × 3, 5 × 5).",
    "• It also performed max pooling.• The output will be concatenated and send to the next inception module.",
    "• Inception V2 • It performs convolutional on the input with 2 different size i.e."
  ]
}